<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Medium-sized. Prostomium 2/3 epilobous. First dorsal pore in 12/13. Three pairs of spermathecal pores in lateroventral intersegments 6/7/8/9. Male pores located inside copulatory pouches in xviii. Male region strongly concave to form an ellipsoid or rounded area. Genital markings absent in the spermathecal region, but two pairs present in 17/18 and 18/19, in line with male pores. Intestinal caeca simple. Holandric. Testis sacs separated. Septa 8/9/10 absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
